Description: Btrfs snapshots + GRUB integration for SysLinuxOS
 Meta-package that integrates snapper, grub-btrfs and the syslinuxos-rollback
 helper to provide automatic GRUB-bootable snapshots with rollback support.
 .
 On install it configures:
   - snapper config 'root' (NUMBER_LIMIT=5, TIMELINE_DAILY=7)
   - grub-btrfs submenu "SysLinuxOS — snapshots", LIMIT=8
   - grub-btrfsd.service + snapper timers enabled
 .
 Provides /usr/bin/syslinuxos-rollback, a helper specific to the Debian-style
 btrfs layout (upstream `snapper rollback` is not supported on Debian).
 .
 Snapshots boot to a text console (GRUB_BTRFS_SNAPSHOT_KERNEL_PARAMETERS=
 systemd.unit=multi-user.target) instead of the graphical display manager,
 giving a uniform recovery environment for MATE and GNOME: log in and run
 syslinuxos-rollback. /etc/profile.d/syslinuxos-snapshot-recovery.sh shows the
 rollback instructions at login when booted from a snapshot.
 .
 Provides /etc/grub.d/13_syslinuxos-btrfs-otheros, a grub-mkconfig helper that
 detects other btrfs installs in subvolume @ layout (Debian #921004, #940710)
 which upstream os-prober fails to identify. Disable with
 GRUB_DISABLE_BTRFS_OTHEROS=true in /etc/default/grub.
 .
 Provides /etc/grub.d/14_syslinuxos-snapshots-otheros, a grub-mkconfig helper
 that exposes snapshots of other SysLinuxOS installs via a chainloaded
 "Advanced" submenu (configfile of the secondary's grub-btrfs.cfg). Disable
 with GRUB_DISABLE_BTRFS_SNAPSHOTS_OTHEROS=true in /etc/default/grub.
 .
 Activates only if rootfs is btrfs. On ext4 the package installs cleanly
 but prints a warning and does not touch the configuration.

